      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Weighty Book</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Allan Rabinowitz letter praises John Updike's June 18 Op-Ed article for reminding readers that real books have value that computers cannot match (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks to John Updike (Op-Ed, June 18) for reminding us that real books have value that computers can't match.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks to John Updike (Op-Ed, June 18) for reminding us that real books have value that computers can't match.</p>
        <p>Add their utility as doorstops, weights, table-levelers and other purely mechanical uses for which there is usually nothing else handy and pocket PC's are worse than useless, and then tell me books are passe!</p>
        <p>ALLAN RABINOWITZ  Los Angeles, June 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
